i think the game is on the line tuesday. we can stand on the sidelines and watch, or we can get into the game,'' waihee told a news conference wednesday, while dukakis listened in from miami, fla., on a telephone conference call
i'm sitting here glowing,'' dukakis said, describing waihee as ``a man who has shown great wisdom in his choice of presidential candidates.''
waihee said the dukakis endorsement has the backing of hawaii's u.s. sens. daniel inouye and spark matsunaga and u.s. rep. daniel akaka, lt. gov. ben cayetano and other democratic leaders
waihee said he is encouraging democrats to vote for dukakis in hawaii's super tuesday precinct elections which will include a presidential preference vote that will be binding on at least 20 of hawaii's 28 delegates to the democratic party national convention
