darden, a democrat from marietta, said in a statement released wednesday s office that he has been impressed by gore's ``strong stand for maintaining a national defense second to none
he realizes that all the rights and privileges guaranteed by the constitution depend on the preservation of our freedom and independence,'' darden said
he is the youngest candidate in the field and the only one who served his country during the vietnam conflict,'' he said. ``he knows firsthand the challenges of low-intensity conflict which america faces in the world today.''
he said he decided that gore offers ``the best overall plan for leading america toward the challenges and opportunities of the 1990s and beyond.''
