alston died wednesday after a short illness
an influential atlanta lawyer, alston raised millions of dollars for the university of georgia and began supporting carter politically after meeting him in 1966
carter lost the governor's race that year to lester maddox, but alston was chairman of carter's successful gubernatorial bid in 1970. he was chairman of the committee for jimmy carter when carter was elected president in 1976
as president, carter appointed alston ambassador to australia
survivors include his wife, a son, a daughter and five grandchildren
