the agency did not say when the stamp would be issued and gave no other details in its two-sentence dispatch, monitored in cyprus
a japanese man and his filipino wife were arrested on charges of smuggling 15 pistols and 71 bullets into japan, a customs official said thursday
akira taniguchi, 50, and his wife, leticia, 37, were arrested for smuggling in u.s.-made raven arms pistols and bullets hidden in a hollow table, the official said
the table was sent by air freight to tokyo's new international airport at narita on feb. 25, but it was so rough in quality that customs officials inspected it by x-ray, said the official, who would not allow his name to be used
police arrested the couple for violating japan's firearms and swords control law, which carries a maximum penalty of 10 years in prison
angry farmers smeared manure in a government office and smashed its computers to protest a planned levy on fertilizer, police said
a group of about 250 farmers stormed the netherlands manure agency building during a demonstration against the levy in this northern dutch town, said police spokesman eduard vissia
the levy, which is to be monitored by the manure agency, is aimed at curbing the mammoth manure surplus that threatens holland's water supplies
the farmers smeared dung all over the place'' after breaking into the building's computer room, vissia said
the protesters also destroyed computer equipment with farm implements before they were thrown out of the building by riot police, vissia said
no arrests were made. no damage estimate was made, although vissia said it probably ran into the tens of thousands of dollars
the surplus amounts to about 90 million tons produced annually by the netherlands' 14 million pigs, 5 million cows, and 92 million chickens
the oversupply stems directly from the common market farm subsidy system, which until recently stimulated large-scale animal husbandry operations
under the contested plan, farmers are required to pay the equivalent of 13 cents for every kilogram _ 2.2 pounds _ of manure they produce in excess of the permitted 275 pounds per 2{ acres of arable land, according to a spokeswoman for the dutch agriculture ministry
the levy soars to about 25 cents for every kilogram in excess of 440 pounds per 2{ acres
the farmers claim that the measures are punitive and demand that the government adopt and fund a project to distribute the manure more evenly over the netherlands through a system of pipelines
state prosecutors have filed charges against the former head of the agrokomerc company that issued almost $1 billion in uncovered promissory notes, it was reported thursday
state prosecutors filed the charge of making counterrevolutionary threats to socialist property against fikret abdic, 48, the former director of the firm, the official news agency tanjug said
seven of abdic's aides were similarly charged, and four were charged with abusing authority in the economy under especially grave circumstances, tanjug said
abdic was arrested last summer after yugoslav media uncovered the scandal surrounding agrokomerc and its practice of issuing uncovered promissory notes
he has already been charged with threatening the social system and embezzlement of social property. he faces a maximum sentence of 20 years in jail if convicted on all counts
the indictment against him may be altered during the trial, according to yugoslav law. no trial date has yet been set
agrokomerc once employed 13,500 people at its headquarters in velika kladusa and was touted as a model company. it has since laid off many employees and is kept running on loans from the republic of bosnia, where it is located
more than 30 people have been arrested in the agrokomerc scandal and charges may be brought against as many as 200 others
jail sentences of up to seven years have been passed so far on some local officials
a tentative settlement has been reached in the week-old cleveland teachers' strike, a federal mediator said today
i'm happy to say that the school board and the cleveland federation of teachers reached a tentative agreement and will be reporting back to their respective constituencies,'' jack buettner said late this morning. ``the parties will then review the details of the proposal at that time.''
details of the agreement were not disclosed, pending a ratification vote
superintendent al tutela declined to comment on when schools might re-open for the district's nearly 73,000 students
eugene kolach, president of the 5,100-member teachers union, said union negotiators will recommend to the union's executive committee that the tentative agreement be approved
early this morning, members of the cleveland school board said they believed progress was being made toward ending the strike
on tuesday, craig brown, chief negotator for the school board, had said talks seemed to be snagged on the issue of ``career ladder,'' a plan to hinge some pay raises largely on performance evaluations
the union's contract expired in september. teaching salaries range from $17,600 to $37,450, depending on education and experience. the average teacher makes $29,000 annually
tutela said the district's 2,951 non-teaching school employees, such as maintenance workers and janitors, were being laid off this week. the layoffs were to continue during the strike, he said. grafs for 2nd graf pvs; deletes grafs 18-19 pvs, gephardt also ... failing campaign.''</note>
