_dr. ivan toms, a 35-year-old white doctor who has run a clinic in the cape town black township of crossroads since 1980, was sentenced to 630 days in prison for refusing to serve, even as a non-combatant, in the south african defense force. toms said he objected to stationing white conscripts in black townships, in the south african-occupied territory of namibia and in neighboring angola
