federated department stores inc. traces its roots to columbus, ohio, where german immigrant simon lazarus sr. opened a men's clothing store in 1848
since then, the business has evolved into the nation's fifth largest general retailer with more than 650 department stores, supermarkets and specialty and discount stores
the store opened by lazarus developed into f&amp;r lazarus co., a department store chain
in 1929, fred lazarus jr. and simon lazarus, grandsons of the company founder, formed federated department stores with filene's in boston and abraham &amp; straus in brooklyn. bloomingdale's in new york joined three months later
today, the company's divisions also include bullock's, burdine's, foley's, i. magnin and rich's department stores; main street and children's place specialty stores; and gold circle discount stores and ralphs supermarkets
federated was based in columbus for its first 16 years, acting as a holding company for its founders. it moved its headquarters to cincinnati near the end of world war ii and became an operating company
the company rang up sales of $11 billion last year
r.h. macy &amp; co. inc., whose holdings include the largest store in the world, returned to private ownership in early 1986 when a management group bought the nation's 10th biggest general retailer for $3.58 billion
that has been the biggest acquisition of a retailer, although the deal will fall to second if macy succeeds in its bid to acquire federated department stores inc. for $5.25 billion in cash plus securities
macy is widely known for its rivalry with its now defunct new york competitor, gimbel's department store, and as the subject of the perennial christmas movie favorite ``miracle on 34th street.'' the movie centered on macy's popular thanksgiving day parade, which celebrates the arrival of santa claus at macy's flagship store on new york's herald square each year
started in 1858 by rowland hussey macy, a former nantucket whaler who had failed at several earlier attempts in the retailing business, the first macy store in downtown manhattan sold fancy goods and stationery items
the company was acquired in 1896 by isadore and nathan straus, and it began selling stock to the public in 1927 as it expanded into a nationwide operation
macy operates 96 stores in 14 states, including macy's department stores and aeropostale, charter club and morgan taylor's fantasy specialty stores
its macy's store at herald square in new york has 2.151 million square feet of space, making it the world's largest store and as big as some shopping centers
here are some details on the operations of federated department stores inc. and r.h. macy &amp; co., which announced a merger agreement wednesday:
revenues _ $5.21 billion (fiscal year ended aug. 1, 1987)
