publicity about aids has reduced sales of the diet candy ayds by up to a half, so the manufacturer is looking for a new name to beef up its image, the chairman said thursday
the diet suppressant has been on the market for 47 years and remains a profitable product for the dep corp., but sales have dropped by as much as 50 percent over the past few years because of the name association, company chairman robert berglass said
you cannot specifically blame the disease on our product in any way, shape or form. we think it is a negative association and it would be best not to have it associated in any way,'' berglass said in a telephone interview from dep's headquarters, 15 miles south of downtown los angeles
johnson and johnson does not have a problem with band-aid because it has the name couched within what the product is,'' he said
i am sure that if you want to do a study, there are a lot of names out there with aids in it, band-aid, cur-aid,'' berglass said. ``our problem is that our name is just that one word.''
since january, ayds has been marketed in great britain under the new name aydslim. if sales show signs of recovery, the appetite suppressant candy may be sold in the united states under that name later this year
so far, reaction from retailers has been positive, berglass said. but consumer reaction has yet to be determined, he said
he expects consumer reaction to be available within the next few months. most people go on diets in the spring, as they think about summer swim suits, he explained
until the name question is answered, dep, which also makes lavoris mouthwash and topol smoker's toothpaste, has a ``frustrating marketing problem,'' he said
you cannot use the radio and television media to advertise. you are confined to print in reaching the consumer. people are not going to listen to your message when they hear it on a verbal basis. they have to see it. that's why our campaign for the spring will be in print.''
industry analysts disagree over the value of a name change
i think it's a dumb move,'' said charles e. brymer, president of the new york-based product-naming firm, interbrand usa
they should just walk away from the name ayds and relaunch it under a new name,'' brymer said. ``the whole aids issue has become so large that i would not want to market anything under that name.''
if you change the name, you give up the equity,'' said ira bachrach, president of san francisco-based namelab inc. ``besides, the problem with the name is more in the mind of the media than the consumer.''
federal health officials believe about 40,000 americans have acquired immune deficiency syndrome. by 1991, that figure is expected to top 270,000. presidental ..., with 2 grafs on reax to brady report; picks up 4th graf pvs, david ruder ....</note>
the chicago mercantile exchange has raised the margin requirements on its stock-index futures by 2 percentage points in response to a call for better coordination of the country's financial markets, officials said thursday
the change, approved wednesday by the exchange's board of governors, requires traders of the merc's standard &amp; poor's 500 stock-index futures to post payments equal to 15 percent of the value of the contracts being traded, instead of 13 percent as previously
a presidential commission that investigated the october stock market collapse suggested raising margins on stock-index futures as a way of curbing swings in their prices. the wild swings have been blamed for adding to volatility in the stock market
the presidential commission, headed by new york investment banker nicholas brady, found that professionals in the stock market can invest in stocks on a margin of as little as 20 to 25 percent. it said margins in futures should be ``consistent,'' although not necessarily equal
john f. sandner, chairman of the chicago mercantile exchange's board of governors, said in a statement that ``maintaining stock-index futures margin at the 15 percent level will bring the `consistency' sought by the brady commission.''
david ruder, chairman of the securities and exchange commission, has suggested margins of 20 percent to 25 percent on index futures
but wendy lee gramm, the new head of the commodity futures trading commission, which regulates futures markets, said wednesday she saw no need for higher margins on stock-index futures
the chicago mercantile exchange is the nation's largest market for stock-index futures, accounting for more than 80 percent of all contracts traded
stock-index futures are traded by investors who use them to hedge against losses in the stock market as well as speculators who hope to profit by guessing on the direction of the market
texas instruments inc. said thursday it will sell a computer for artificial-intelligence work based on apple computer inc.'s macintosh ii, a step that should move ``thinking machines'' more into the mainstream of business
texas instruments said the new micro explorer would have all the functions of a standard macintosh ii as well as artificial-intelligence features, such as the ability to manipulate symbols instead of just numbers
most other artificial-intelligence (ai) workstations, including texas instruments' own explorer, cannot be used as general-purpose computers
other ai companies are also moving to insert their technology into existing computers, including texas instruments' biggest rival in the field, symbolics inc. of cambridge, mass
however, cupertino, calif.-based apple said it will have an especially close relationship with dallas-based texas instruments. in a first for both companies, texas instruments and apple will both put their logos on the micro explorer, which will be marketed only by texas instruments
texas instruments and apple said the micro explorer could be used in such varied fields as tax advising, computer-aided design and assigning gates to airplanes at airports
although artificial intelligence encompasses the whole concept of making computers think like people, most products on the market have the more modest goal of augmenting human decision makers by converting knowledge into a set of rules that can be applied by a computer
the price of the micro explorer ranges from about $15,000 to $30,000, compared to $50,000 to $70,000 for the explorer, which is about twice as powerful, texas instruments said. an ai package will also be available for people who already own the mac ii. shipments are scheduled to begin in the april-june period
symbolics, in a response to the texas instruments announcement, said its ivory chip for artificial intelligence is superior to texas instruments' explorer lisp chip. it also said its chip will be plugged into not only the mac ii, but also international business machines corp.'s personal system-2 and pc at, although it could not give a timetable
texas instruments said it had no timetable for putting its artificial-intelligence chip into other personal computers besides the mac ii
royal dutch-shell group of companies reported thursday that its profit rose 14 percent in both the fourth quarter and all of 1987, but the world's largest oil company would have suffered a decrease for the year under accounting rules used in the united states
the anglo-dutch oil giant said after-tax earnings for the final three months of 1987 totaled 858 british pounds, or about $1.5 billion, compared with a profit of 752 pounds a year earlier. it attributed the improvement to gains in exploration, production and chemical businesses that offset lower refinery profits
revenue fell 37.6 percent to 1.34 billion pounds from 2.15 billion pounds, a drop attributed largely to asset sales and movements in net working capital during the year-earlier period, the company said
for the full year, royal dutch-shell said it had an after-tax profit of 2.88 billion pounds, or about $4.74 billion, compared with earnings of 2.54 billion pounds in 1986. revenue decreased 29.3 percent to 5.3 billion pounds from 7.5 billion pounds
royal dutch-shell uses an accounting system that values inventories on a ``first-in, first-out basis,'' as opposed to the ``last-in, first-out'' basis used by most major american oil companies
the company said that if it had used the american accounting system, its full-year results would have shown a 15 percent decline in profit _ dropping to 2.86 billion pounds, or about $4.73 billion, from 3.37 billion pounds
for the fourth-quarter, however, its profit would have been ever better under the american rules, showing a 64 percent rise. its earnings for the quarter totaled 986 million pounds, or about $1.71 billion, compared with a profit of 600 million pounds a year earlier
with headquarters in london and the hague, netherlands, royal dutch-shell is the largest oil company in the world. it is the parent of shell oil co., based in houston
roxane laboratories inc. has recalled six lot numbers of its roxanol 100 pain reliever because of a possibly defective spoon that the company said could result in an overdose of morphine
the recall, announced wednesday, is for lots 860503, 860828, 870289, 870521, 870860 and 871027 of roxanol 100, a liquid form of morphine sulfate prescribed for the relief of severe pain in terminally ill cancer patients
the company said there is no problem with the drug itself and that no injuries have been reported to date. the product is distributed nationwide
a similar product called roxanol, which is dispensed with a dropper, is not involved in the recall, the company said
the company said a defective spoon was discovered in display samples of roxanol 100. the defective spoon has a cylindrical tube, from top to bottom, into which medication is poured for measurement; the correct spoon has a plug in the tube just below the 20mg mark, and the lower third of the tube just below the plug is open on the back side
roxane laboratories estimated the risk of the defective spoon appearing in a package of roxanol 100 at about 1 in 1,000, but requested that hospitals, pharmacies and wholesalers that have the lot numbers in question return the packages to roxane laboratories for inspection. the company said replacement stock is available
the company also urged pharmacists and other health care professionals to consult with patients using roxanol 100 and determine if any defective spoons are in their possession
patients taking the drug should consult with pharmacists or other health professionals, the company said. roxane laboratories said it would supply a replacement spoon in cases where spoons are found to be defective, or that replacements could be supplied by pharmacists or physicians
eds: the address for roxane laboratories is 1809 wilson road, columbus, ohio, 43228
