hilton hotels corp. said thursday it has been approached by a japanese investor about the possibility of selling its 22-acre hilton hawaiian village on waikiki beach
however, the company's chairman and chief executive, barron hilton, denied a report that the investors had offered $1 billion, noting that price would equate to about $340,000 a room, which is less than other hotels in hawaii have fetched
he also noted that the company has recently spent $100 million refurbishing the 2,524-room complex, which is owned jointly with prudential insurance co. of america
hilton didn't identify the investors, but said that the overtures were unsolicited and that no formal discussions had been held
the hotel is not on the market. we do not feel it is in the best interest of our company to sell the village at this time,'' hilton said
his statement did not address a report in the wall street journal on thursday that the investors also were interested in acquiring the company's waldorf-astoria hotel in new york, and a company spokesman declined to elaborate
hilton is sole owner of the waldorf, which also has recently undergone an expensive refurbishing
the hawaiian village and waldorf have turned in especially strong earnings in recent periods, the company has said
late last year, the company sold the 592-room beverly hilton to entertainer-businessman merv griffin for $100.2 million. the beverly hills property also was jointly owned by hilton and prudential. report are for week ended tuesday. all other figures are for the week ended wednesday.</note>
assets of the nation's 418 money market mutual funds fell $1.15 billion in the latest week, the investment company institute said thursday
the decline, to $278.51 billion in the seven-day period ended wednesday, followed a revised $2.59 billion increase in the funds' assets the previous week, according to the washington-based mutual fund trade group. that rise, in the week ended feb. 24, put the funds' assets at a record high of $280.02 billion
the investment company institute said that in the latest week, assets of 208 general purpose funds rose $230.5 million to $81.67 billion, assets of 97 broker-dealer funds dropped $457.8 million to $115.10 billion, and assets of 113 institutional funds decreased $1.28 billion to $81.74 billion
the seven-day average yield on money market mutual funds fell in the week ended tuesday to 6.10 percent from 6.16 percent the previous week, according to donoghue's money fund report, a trade journal based in holliston, mass
the 30-day average yield fell to 6.17 percent from 6.23 percent, donoghue's said
the average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 45 days, up from 43 days, donoghue's said
separately, the newsletter bank rate monitor said its survey of 100 leading commercial banks, savings and loan assocations and savings banks in the nation's 10 largest markets showed the effective annual yield available on money market accounts fell to 5.74 percent as of wednesday from 5.75 percent a week earlier
the north palm beach, fla.-based newsletter said the effective annual yield available on special savings accounts, called super now accounts, were unchanged at 5.17 percent
bank rate monitor said the effective annual yield was 6.85 percent on six-month certificates of deposit, down from 6.88 percent the previous week. yields were 7.16 percent on 1-year cds, down from 7.20 percent; 7.57 percent on 2{-year cds, down from 7.62 percent; and 8.04 percent on 5-year cds, down from 8.08 percent
